cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the visual system of flying insects and proposes a STMD-based visual system for small target motion detection. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the neural layers and feedback loops in the STMD pathway. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper discusses the challenge of discriminating small moving objects for autonomous micro robots. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper discusses the functional roles of feedback loops in motion perception. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new visual system with feedback connection and compares its properties with the existing STMD-based models.
